    "scenes": [
        {
            "id": "s1",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "Overview",
                "body": "<p>You might know the Matterhorn as a mountain in the Swiss Alps, or as one of the best rides at Disneyland. At Pandora, Matterhorn is a reservation request system!</p><p>Let’s learn what Matterhorn is and when to use it. During your next check-in, ask your TA to give you a demonstration of how to use this tool for your campaigns. </p>",
                "class": "align-center-wide"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "img-1",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0,
                        "right": "80%",
                        "ease": "Back.easeOut"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "img-1",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s2",
            "bg_color": "#44aade",
            "text": {
                "header": "What is Matterhorn?",
                "body": "<p>Matterhorn is an internal reservation request system managed by PYM. Client Services uses this tool for campaigns that have heavy-ups, takeovers and/or sponsorship opportunities. Don't know what those terms mean? It's okay, we'll get to that in a little bit!</p><p>After Client Services requests a reservation, PYM can approve or deny it. They decide using a lot of different variables, like revenue and competing reservations. </p>",
                "class": "align-center-wide"
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "img-1",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0,
                        "right": "80%",
                        "ease": "Back.easeOut"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "img-1",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0.0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s3",
            "bg_color": "#993333",
            "text": {
                "header": "Who uses Matterhorn?",
                "body": "<p>Some client services teams might use Matterhorn for different purposes. Let's see how your team uses Matterhorn for your campaigns!</p><p class='pt-callout'>Click on the microphones to see how different teams at Pandora use Matterhorn for their campaigns.</p>",
                "class": "align-left"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_matterhorn_s3",
                "id": "cr-matterhorn-s3",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "National, Local and Inside teams",
                        "body": "<p>These teams use Matterhorn to request impression reservations. If PYM approves their request, client services can move forward with their campaign. If PYM denies their request, whoever submitted the Matterhorn request needs to withdraw it.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Performance team",
                        "body": "<p>Account managers track Matterhorn's calendar to see which ad products are in high demand. Matterhorn lets them narrow down sponsorship reservations for specific products and demos. That's how account managers can optimize campaigns and make better product recommendations. Pretty cool, right?</p>"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "cr-matterhorn-s3",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "cr-matterhorn-s3 .reveal-item",
                    "type": "staggerFrom",
                    "duration": 0.3,
                    "startTime": 0.8,
                    "staggerOffset": 0.15,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                }
            ],
            "leave": [
                {
                    "id": "cr-matterhorn-s3",
                    "type": "to",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "cr-matterhorn-s3 .reveal-item",
                    "type": "staggerTo",
                    "duration": 0.3,
                    "startTime": 0.8,
                    "staggerOffset": 0.15,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s4",
            "bg_color": "#993333",
            "text": {
                "header": "When to use Matterhorn?",
                "body": "<p>So… when’s the right time to put in a reservation request? Usually, this happens in the pre-sale phase of your deal (duh).</p><p class='pt-callout'>Play the trumpet to learn more.</p>",
                "class": "align-right"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_matterhorn_s4",
                "id": "cr-matterhorn-s4",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "Developing a Media Mix",
                        "body": "<p>While developing media plans, your pod might recommend a solution that requires a Matterhorn reservation. For instance, you may want to recommend a sponsorship product to your client. Or, you may want to recommend a product with a high share of voice.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Client Services",
                        "body": "<p>Campaign specialists create Matterhorn requests. This happens soon after account executives create Salesforce opportunities. </p><p>You can't pitch a campaign without making sure the impressions are available. You can only pitch your campaign after PYM approves your Matterhorn reservation request. If the client is accepts your plan, these impressions are yours to book! </p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "A Request is not a Reservation",
                        "body": "<p>Booking a Matterhorn request doesn't guarantee a reservation. Other pods may book competing reservations with your opportunity. PYM will look at all requests and decide which to approve between conflicting reservations. That's why it's important to book your request as early in the pre-sale process as possible.</p>"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "enter": [
                {
                    "id": "cr-matterhorn-s4",
                    "type": "from",
                    "duration": 0.5,
                    "startTime": 0.3,
                    "props": {
                        "autoAlpha": 0
                    }
                },
                {
