                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "s5",
            "bg_color": "#993333",
            "text": {
                "header": "Matterhorn Reservation Types",
                "body": "<p>What's the difference between a takeover and heavy-up? What's a Pandora sponsorship and a DFP sponsorship? Let's explore what these terms mean, and how they fit into Matterhorn!</p><p class='pt-callout'>Play the sax to learn more about each Matterhorn reservation type.</p>",
                "class": "align-center-wide"
            },
            "interaction": {
                "name": "cr_matterhorn_s5",
                "id": "cr-matterhorn-s5",
                "type": "clickReveal",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "header": "Takeovers",
                        "body": "<p>Takeovers are ad products that have a 100 percent share of voice. Takeover products include animated overlays, interstitials, billboards, first impressions and front door takeovers.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Heavy Ups",
                        "body": "<p>A heavy up is a way of saying that your ad product will have a share of voice, or SOV, higher than what PYM recommends. That means an SOV higher than 20 percent for audio products and 30 percent for non-audio products.</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "Genre Stations",
                        "body": "<p>It's time to break out the Pandora Latin Christmas genre station, and get our eggnog on! But only one advertiser can sponsor a genre station at a time. And we have a limited amount of genre stations. That's why you'll need to request a genre station reservation in Matterhorn!</p><p>The genre stations type here aren't just seasonal, like the Black History Month stations. You can also request reservations for ongoing genre stations, like a decades station!</p>"
                    },
                    {
                        "header": "New Initiatives",
                        "body": "<p>We're always coming out with new ways to delight advertisers and listeners. For example, Pandora was the first streaming service to provide Serial season 2! We even created native ad experiences like Sponsored Listening that only we can provide. Some clients jump at the chance to advertise with these new products. The demand may be way higher than the supply. That's why PYM sets up a reservation requests for new initiatives.</p>"
                    }
                ]
            },
